(18, 17, E'# StarLoop - Turn Happy Diners into Five-Star Reviews, Automatically\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nStarLoop is a review generation and reputation monitoring platform designed specifically for independent restaurant owners. The product''s approach is uniquely proactive: instead of waiting for customers to voluntarily leave reviews, StarLoop uses a post-meal QR flow that catches customers in their peak satisfaction moment (right after a good meal) and converts that positive emotion into a Google review in under 45 seconds. Simultaneously, unhappy customers are routed to a private feedback channel, giving the owner a chance to make it right before a 1-star review appears online.\n\n**Tagline**: Your happiest diners are your best marketers. StarLoop connects them to Google in 45 seconds.\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Dimension | Statistic | Implication |\n|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| US independent restaurants | ~500,000 | Massive addressable market |\n| Avg Google reviews per independent | ~35 | Far below chain averages |\n| Consumer trust: reviews same as personal rec | 88% | BrightLocal 2023 |\n| Revenue lift per 1-star increase (Yelp) | +5-9% | Harvard Business School |\n| Restaurants responding to reviews | <30% | Industry survey |\n| Time owners spend on review management | 2-4 hrs/week | Owner interviews |\n| Restaurants using paid review tools | <15% | Podium internal |\n| TAM (review management software) | ~$600M/yr | 500k × ~$1,200/yr |\n\n**Opportunity**: Only 15% tool penetration + clear ROI (star ratings directly map to revenue) = strong pull market once owners see a demo.\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Competitor | Type | Price/mo | Critical Gap |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| Podium | SMS-based review platform | $399-$599 | Too expensive; SMS feels intrusive |\n| Birdeye | Full reputation suite | $299-$499 | SMB-unfriendly pricing and complexity |\n| Broadly | Local business reputation | $199-$299 | No restaurant-specific workflow |\n| NiceJob | Review automation | $75-$149 | Not restaurant-native; no QR/table flow |\n| ReviewTrackers | Review monitoring | $119-$239 | Monitoring only, no generation |\n| **StarLoop** | **QR-native, restaurant-specific** | **$69-$139** | **New brand; QR approach is novel** |\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n### Persona A: Linda - The Overwhelmed Owner-Operator\n- **Age**: 49, female, suburban Ohio\n- **Restaurant**: Family diner, 22 years in business, 85 seats\n- **Review situation**: 4.1 stars on Google, 41 reviews over 22 years\n- **Pain points**:\n  1. Has no system to ask for reviews; feels awkward asking in person\n  2. Got a 2-star review last month that she believes was unfair; doesn''t know how to respond\n  3. Watches a newer competitor across the street accumulate reviews faster\n- **What she wants**: Something simple that works without her having to think about it daily\n- **Tech level**: Basic — uses a tablet POS, checks Facebook occasionally\n- **Price threshold**: $69-$89/month maximum\n\n### Persona B: James - The Competitive Fine Dining Chef-Owner\n- **Age**: 38, male, Boston MA\n- **Restaurant**: Modern American, 60 seats, $85 avg check, 4.6 stars\n- **Situation**: Already has good reviews but wants to maintain and grow his rating as he prepares for a second location\n- **Specific need**: Sentiment analysis to catch service issues before they become public; competitive benchmarking against nearby fine dining\n- **Tech level**: High; uses OpenTable, 7shifts for scheduling, Square for POS\n- **Willingness to pay**: $129-$139/month for full feature set\n\n### Persona C: Maria - The Recent Immigrant Restaurateur\n- **Age**: 44, female, Chicago IL\n- **Restaurant**: Authentic Mexican, 2 years open, loyal neighborhood following\n- **Problem**: Customers love the food and tell her in person but don''t leave reviews; her Google page has 28 reviews while the chain Tex-Mex nearby has 380\n- **Language**: English as second language; needs simple, clear UI and templates in both English and Spanish\n- **Willingness to pay**: $69-$79/month if setup is handled for her\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Priority | Feature | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| P0 | QR table insert generator | Printable QR codes linking to branded review flow |\n| P0 | Satisfaction gate | 1-3 stars → private form; 4-5 stars → Google review link |\n| P0 | Google Business API integration | Sync all reviews to dashboard automatically |\n| P0 | Private feedback inbox | Unhappy diner messages go here; owner can reply privately |\n| P0 | Response template library | 15+ restaurant-specific templates for positive and negative responses |\n| P1 | Yelp integration | Sync Yelp reviews to unified dashboard |\n| P1 | Sentiment tagging | Auto-tag review themes: food, service, ambiance, value, wait time |\n| P1 | Weekly reputation digest email | Summary of new reviews, rating trend, suggested actions |\n| P1 | AI response drafts | One-click draft generation per review (owner approves before posting) |\n| P2 | Spanish language UI | Full Spanish localization for owner dashboard and QR landing page |\n| P2 | Staff shoutout tracking | Identify which servers are mentioned positively in reviews |\n| P2 | Competitor tracking | Monitor rating trends for up to 5 nearby competitors |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n```\nFrontend:\n  - Owner dashboard: React 18 + TailwindCSS\n  - Customer QR landing page: Vanilla HTML/CSS + minimal JS\n    - No framework overhead; must load <800ms on 4G\n    - Hosted on CDN (Cloudflare Pages)\n\nBackend:\n  - Go + Echo v4\n  - Google Business Profile API v4 (OAuth for review read/reply)\n  - Yelp Fusion API (read-only review pull)\n  - OpenAI API (GPT-4o-mini for response drafting, sentiment tagging)\n  - QR generation: go-qrcode library\n  - Cron: Hourly review sync, daily digest generation\n\nData:\n  - PostgreSQL 16 (restaurants, reviews, private feedback, response history)\n  - Redis (rate limiting, API response cache)\n\nNotifications:\n  - SendGrid (weekly digest, negative review instant alert)\n  - Twilio (SMS alert for 1-star reviews — owner can opt in)\n\nCard PDF:\n  - Puppeteer (generate printable QR card designs)\n```\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Plan | Price | Features | Target |\n|------|-------|---------|--------|\n| Grow | $69/mo | QR system, satisfaction gate, Google integration, template library | New/small restaurants |\n| Pro | $109/mo | + Yelp, sentiment tagging, AI drafts, weekly digest | Established independents |\n| Elite | $139/mo | + competitor tracking, staff shoutouts, multi-location (up to 3) | Growth-stage operators |\n| Setup fee | $49 one-time | Design + print 10 QR table cards, onboarding call | All plans |\n\n**Revenue logic**: Setup fee reduces churn risk (sunk cost keeps them engaged through the learning curve) and funds actual onboarding quality.\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Phase | Duration | Focus | Gate Metric |\n|-------|----------|-------|-------------|\n| M1: QR + Gate | 4 weeks | QR landing page, satisfaction gate, private feedback | 8 restaurants in beta |\n| M2: Dashboard | 3 weeks | Google integration, review list, response templates | Avg response rate >50% |\n| M3: Intelligence | 4 weeks | Sentiment tagging, AI drafts, weekly digest | Owner active sessions ≥3/week |\n| M4: Launch | 3 weeks | Billing, Yelp, setup service, referral program | 40 paying restaurants |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| KPI | 3-Month | 6-Month |\n|-----|---------|--------|\n| Registered restaurants | 120 | 350 |\n| Paid subscribers | 50 | 175 |\n| MRR | $4,500 | $17,500 |\n| Avg new reviews/month per restaurant | 12 (vs. 3 baseline) | 18 |\n| Avg star rating change (after 3 months) | +0.2 | +0.4 |\n| Private feedback intercept rate | ≥20% of unhappy | ≥28% |\n| Owner NPS | ≥48 | ≥55 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Severity | Probability | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|-------------|------------|\n| Google changes review API access | High | Low-medium | Monitor API changelog; build Yelp integration as hedge; manual import CSV fallback |\n| Restaurant owners don''t train staff on QR | High | High | Provide laminated staff briefing cards; include in setup service |\n| Satisfaction gate seen as review manipulation | Medium | Low | Transparent language on landing page; not hiding reviews, redirecting unhappy feedback |\n| High churn if rating doesn''t improve fast | High | Medium | Set realistic expectations in onboarding: 90-day trajectory, not overnight |\n| Podium drops price to compete | Medium | Low | Our restaurant-native workflow and QR approach remain differentiated at any price point |',
    E'[{"step":"Review timing","decision":"QR at table (peak satisfaction moment) vs. SMS after meal","reason":"Post-meal SMS feels intrusive and arrives when satisfaction has already faded; QR at table captures emotion at its peak, drives higher conversion"},{"step":"Pricing","decision":"$69 Grow entry tier with $49 setup fee","reason":"$69 monthly removes the primary objection for small restaurants; one-time setup fee creates sunk cost that reduces early churn and funds real onboarding quality"},{"step":"AI responses","decision":"Draft-approve flow, not auto-post","reason":"A response posted in a restaurant owner''s name that sounds robotic can damage trust more than not responding; owners must control their voice"},{"step":"Localization","decision":"Spanish UI as P2 priority","reason":"Hispanic-owned restaurants are a significant underserved segment; even basic Spanish support opens a differentiated acquisition channel"},{"step":"Competitive tracking","decision":"Limit to 5 nearby competitors in Elite plan","reason":"Owners are primarily concerned with their immediate neighborhood; global benchmarking is a feature creep trap"},{"step":"Go-to-market","decision":"Local restaurant association partnerships + direct outreach to owners with 3.5-4.2 star ratings","reason":"The 3.5-4.2 star segment has the most urgent pain and clearest ROI case; sub-3.5 stars often have deeper operational issues beyond review management"}]',
    'submitted', 37, NOW() - INTERVAL '8 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '9 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '8 days'),

